{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"hidden"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A hidden view."}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hidden views are invisible and can’t receive or respond to interactions."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, they do remain in the view hierarchy and affect layout. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this modifier if you want to include a view for layout purposes, but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"don’t want it to display."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["HStack {","    Image(systemName: \"a.circle.fill\")","    Image(systemName: \"b.circle.fill\")","    Image(systemName: \"c.circle.fill\")","        .hidden()","    Image(systemName: \"d.circle.fill\")","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The third circle takes up space, because it’s still present, but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"OpenSwiftUI doesn’t draw it onscreen.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to conditionally include a view in the view hierarchy, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an ","type":"text"},{"code":"if","type":"